      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Maximum Security Adolescent</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Judy DiBerardino-Barnhart letter on Margaret Talbot's September 10 article questions how children can be rehabilitated in jail (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>We tell kids to keep out of gangs, stay away from drugs and then, when they get into trouble, we put them into a society of gangs and drugs. Adults are not rehabilitated in jail; how can a child be? When children really need help, when they need the guidance of an adult, we give them murderers and drug dealers to serve as their guides in the prison system.</p>
        <p>Judy DiBerardino-  Barnhart  New York</p>
      </block>
